## Example Usage

### Basic Load
```python
seismic = geox_load_seismic_line(
    filepath="/data/malay_basin_3d.zgy",
    crs="EPSG:32648",
    survey_id="MB_2024_3D"
)
# Returns in ~2 seconds (metadata only)
```

### Subset Load (Processing Window)
```python
seismic_subset = geox_load_seismic_line(
    filepath="/data/malay_basin_3d.zgy",
    crs="EPSG:32648",
    survey_id="MB_2024_3D",
    inline_range=[500, 1500],
    xline_range=[1200, 1800],
    time_range_ms=[1500, 3500]
)
# Loads only 1001x601 traces, 2000ms window
# Reduces memory by ~85%
```

### Reprojection (Advanced)
```python
seismic_wgs84 = geox_load_seismic_line(
    filepath="/data/malay_basin_3d.zgy",
    crs="EPSG:32648",  // source CRS from file
    target_crs="EPSG:4326",  // reproject to WGS84
    survey_id="MB_2024_3D_WGS84"
)
```

